  "stage": {
    "id": "stage_3_train_and_run",
    "stageNumber": 3,
    "title": "Stage 3: Train It & Run It",
    "roomWidth": 20,
    "roomHeight": 15,
    "concepts": [
      {
        "id": "training_loop",
        "title": "The Training Recipe",
        "content": "Key ideas:\n- warmup schedule\n- label smoothing ε=0.1\n\nVaswani et al. use Adam (β₁=0.9, β₂=0.98) with lrate=d_model^{-0.5}·min(step^{-0.5}, step·warmup^{-1.5}). Warmup lets the model stabilize before large gradient updates; label smoothing ε=0.1 improves generalization.",
        "position": {
          "x": 7,
          "y": 6
        },
        "type": "text"
      },
      {
        "id": "inference_decoding",
        "title": "Generating Text: Beam Search & KV Cache",
        "content": "Key ideas:\n- beam search\n- KV cache\n\nThe encoder runs once over the source; the decoder generates autoregressively using beam search (beam=4, α=0.6 length penalty). KV caching stores past key/value pairs so each new token only attends forward — the basis of efficient LLM inference today.",
        "position": {
          "x": 11,
          "y": 6
        },
        "type": "text"
      }
    ],
    "quiz": {
      "id": "quiz-stage-3",
      "question": "At inference, you can cache the encoder's output and only run the decoder for each new token. What does this optimization save? Answer with a number.",
      "type": "multiple-choice",
      "options": [
        "Recomputing attention over the source sentence every step",
        "Recomputing token embeddings",
        "Recomputing layer normalization"
      ],
      "correctAnswer": "Recomputing attention over the source sentence every step",
